WEBVTT

00:02.380 --> 00:04.880
Previously
on "Grey's Anatomy"...

00:04.880 --> 00:06.080
April:
Jackson. He likes you.

00:06.080 --> 00:07.580
He has feelings for you.
You should just tell him.

00:07.580 --> 00:09.040
You want to go have
some overly tired sex?

00:09.040 --> 00:10.330
I just got fired.

00:10.330 --> 00:11.830
Owen: Two soldiers
came to the house today.

00:11.830 --> 00:14.330
They said they found Megan.
They said that she's alive.

00:14.330 --> 00:16.170
Meredith: Remember the dream
where they come back to us?

00:16.170 --> 00:18.380
-Megan's alive?
-Megan's alive.

00:18.380 --> 00:21.250
If this were Derek,
I would already be gone.

00:23.000 --> 00:25.000
[ Helicopter blades whirring ]

00:29.880 --> 00:32.210
Meredith:
A painful irony for doctors

00:32.210 --> 00:33.960
is that we often
have to make you sicker

00:33.960 --> 00:35.670
in order to heal you.

00:35.670 --> 00:37.120
Megan?

00:39.540 --> 00:40.620
Megan.

00:44.830 --> 00:46.750
Who -- Who are you?

00:51.460 --> 00:54.290
Sorry. [ Laughs ]
I had to do it.

00:54.290 --> 00:55.620
[ Both laugh ]

00:55.620 --> 00:57.000
Will you unstrap me
from this thing

00:57.000 --> 00:58.460
so I can hug your
ridiculously pale body?

00:58.460 --> 01:00.380
Yeah.

01:00.380 --> 01:01.710
[ Belt clicks ]

01:01.710 --> 01:02.620
Come here.

01:04.620 --> 01:07.960
If a bone has healed unevenly,
we have to rebreak it.

01:09.580 --> 01:11.500
If a scar is too thick,

01:11.500 --> 01:15.210
we have to scrape it off
and create a new wound.

01:18.830 --> 01:23.460
We break you down
to rebuild you.

01:23.460 --> 01:25.380
Megan: I was not kept
in that hole.

01:25.380 --> 01:28.250
I was tossed in the hole
when the bombing started.

01:28.250 --> 01:30.170
They were trying
to protect me.

01:30.170 --> 01:32.830
Trauma surgeons aren't
easy to come by in Iraq.

01:32.830 --> 01:35.080
-So all these years, you --
-I was treated really well.

01:35.080 --> 01:37.830
They'd just, you know,
kill me if I left.

01:37.830 --> 01:39.500
Your wife
is really pretty.

01:39.500 --> 01:41.210
I'm really happy
to meet you.

01:41.210 --> 01:43.330
Me too.
[ Chuckles softly ]

01:46.380 --> 01:48.790
Hey, stranger.
[ Chuckles softly ]

01:48.790 --> 01:50.670
[ Sobbing ]

01:52.920 --> 01:54.620
[ Inhales sharply ]

01:54.620 --> 01:57.120
I'm so sorry.

01:57.120 --> 02:00.040
Shh. Babe, it's okay.
It's okay. I'm okay.

02:00.040 --> 02:01.540
I'm --

02:01.540 --> 02:03.210
Okay, ow.
You're gonna have to --

02:03.210 --> 02:04.290
Ow.

02:04.290 --> 02:05.620
-What hurts?
-What's wrong?

02:05.620 --> 02:08.120
There was a bombing
six months ago.

02:08.120 --> 02:10.290
I...took some shrapnel.

02:10.290 --> 02:12.210
There were
post-op complications.

02:12.210 --> 02:14.830
It didn't heal so well.

02:16.040 --> 02:21.500
♪♪

02:21.500 --> 02:27.670
♪♪

02:27.670 --> 02:31.380
Okay. Um, all right, everyone!
Listen up, please!

02:31.380 --> 02:33.880
Uh, first,
I want to thank you all

02:33.880 --> 02:36.420
for keeping your heads
during the events of last night.

02:36.420 --> 02:40.500
Thanks to you, there were
very minimal injuries,

02:40.500 --> 02:43.790
and the firefighters were able
to contain the blaze quickly.

02:43.790 --> 02:47.960
There was some damage, however,
that will need to be repaired.

02:47.960 --> 02:52.880
Uh, the neuro ICU, the cath lab,
and pulmonary clinic...

02:52.880 --> 02:54.670
[ Clears throat ]

02:54.670 --> 02:56.540
[ Hushed voice ]
She fired Eliza.

02:56.540 --> 02:57.830
[ Hushed voice ]
Oh, yeah. I heard.

02:57.830 --> 03:00.080
Just give her some room.
Getting fired is humiliating.

03:00.080 --> 03:01.330
How much room?

03:01.330 --> 03:03.250
Like, hours or days?

03:03.250 --> 03:04.960
...and endoscopy suites...

03:04.960 --> 03:06.960
I've never been fired.

03:06.960 --> 03:09.290
These stations will
be off-limits to
pedestrian foot traffic.

03:09.290 --> 03:11.210
Stephanie's gone.

03:11.210 --> 03:15.750
She was airlifted to
a burn center in Texas.

03:15.750 --> 03:17.500
So until further notice,

03:17.500 --> 03:20.830
ORs 3 through 6
are nonfunctional.

03:20.830 --> 03:22.330
Hunt,
your sister's here?

03:22.330 --> 03:24.040
Yeah, Riggs
is taking her to CT.

03:24.040 --> 03:27.170
Uh, Riggs and I, we're gonna
need to take some leave.

03:27.170 --> 03:29.210
Understood.
I'll update Bailey.

03:29.210 --> 03:31.000
Uh, your sister will be
our first priority

03:31.000 --> 03:32.920
as soon as we're done here.
Okay. Thanks.

03:32.920 --> 03:37.620
To recap, we are to avoid
ORs 3 through 6

03:37.620 --> 03:40.540
and the entire neuro wing,
as they are unstable.

03:40.540 --> 03:41.830
[ Clatter ]

03:41.830 --> 03:43.960
[ Indistinct shouting ]

03:48.210 --> 03:51.170
And also avoid
fourth-floor nurses station

03:51.170 --> 03:54.580
until further notice.

04:01.380 --> 04:04.080
[ Telephone rings ]

04:04.080 --> 04:05.080
Hey.

04:05.080 --> 04:07.670
-Hey.
-You're working?

04:07.670 --> 04:10.080
Yeah, I'm gonna work.

04:11.380 --> 04:12.580
How's Megan?

04:12.580 --> 04:15.170
Uh, she's alive.

04:15.170 --> 04:16.620
And -- well,
not quite well,

04:16.620 --> 04:20.420
but she's funny and sharp
and very much alive,

04:20.420 --> 04:22.710
which is,
you know, energizing.

04:22.710 --> 04:25.580
I mean, this miracle happened,
and it makes me aware

04:25.580 --> 04:28.080
that I have the ability
to make that miracle happen

04:28.080 --> 04:30.960
for someone else's family,
so...yeah.

04:30.960 --> 04:33.080
I'm gonna work.

04:33.080 --> 04:35.290
You don't think
you should be with Owen today?

04:35.290 --> 04:37.080
You know what --
I'm super-good in a crisis,

04:37.080 --> 04:38.290
but the crisis is over.

04:38.290 --> 04:39.420
[ Cabinet door closes ]

04:43.880 --> 04:45.380
[ Door closes ]

04:45.380 --> 04:46.580
[ Whirring ]

04:46.580 --> 04:48.500
And you've been here
for how long?

04:48.500 --> 04:50.670
Couple years now.

04:51.920 --> 04:54.750
And have you met anyone...

04:54.750 --> 04:56.620
you know, significant?

04:58.040 --> 04:59.040
Hey.

04:59.040 --> 05:00.750
Oh, h-hang one sec, Meg.

05:00.750 --> 05:02.460
-Hey.
-Hey.

05:02.460 --> 05:04.000
How is she doing?

05:04.000 --> 05:09.080
Oh, she's, um, got
a frozen abdomen, but...

05:09.080 --> 05:12.460
You know, all things considered,
she's pretty okay.

05:12.460 --> 05:14.210
That's great.

05:14.210 --> 05:15.380
And how are you?

05:15.380 --> 05:19.500
Yeah, all things considered,
pretty okay.

05:19.500 --> 05:20.500
You?

05:20.500 --> 05:22.080
Same.

05:29.420 --> 05:31.710
Hey, sorry, Meg.
Where were we?

05:31.710 --> 05:33.790
I was asking
if you met anyone,

05:33.790 --> 05:36.080
and you were buying time
to come up with
an acceptable answer.

05:36.080 --> 05:37.750
I wasn't buying time.
Liar.

05:37.750 --> 05:40.040
Look. Uh...

05:40.040 --> 05:41.960
I-I did meet someone.

05:43.540 --> 05:45.040
And?

05:45.040 --> 05:47.580
And...she's not you.

05:49.170 --> 05:51.460
Smooth.

05:51.460 --> 05:52.460
Right?

05:52.460 --> 05:54.330
[ Both laugh ]

05:54.330 --> 05:56.540
The southwest wing of the
second floor has been cleared,

05:56.540 --> 05:58.380
so all of the patients
in beds 3 through 10

05:58.380 --> 06:00.120
can be transported
back upstairs, okay?

06:00.120 --> 06:02.790
-DeLuca, what do you got?
-Beau Martinez, 14 years old.

06:02.790 --> 06:04.120
Presents with
intense jaw pain

06:04.120 --> 06:05.380
and recurrent
left-sided headaches.

06:05.380 --> 06:06.420
Beau, can you follow
my finger?

06:06.420 --> 06:07.830
Good.

06:07.830 --> 06:09.920
-When did the pain start?
-A few months ago.

06:09.920 --> 06:12.250
They took these X-rays
last month. They saw nothing.

06:12.250 --> 06:13.620
They gave him pain pills
that don't work,

06:13.620 --> 06:15.330
and now they won't give him
any more 'cause --

06:15.330 --> 06:17.170
They treat him like he's
a drug addict or something.

06:17.170 --> 06:19.000
That's not my kid.

06:19.000 --> 06:20.830
He can't even
play baseball anymore.

06:20.830 --> 06:23.620
He says it's a stabbing pain
in the jaw and mastoid area.

06:23.620 --> 06:24.960
Thought maybe we should get

06:24.960 --> 06:27.000
a head, cervical,
maxillofacial CT.

06:27.000 --> 06:28.040
Agreed.

06:28.040 --> 06:30.080
Beau, I've got you.

06:30.080 --> 06:31.920
I know this pain is real,
and I am not gonna rest

06:31.920 --> 06:34.040
until we find out what it is
and how to fix it.

06:34.040 --> 06:35.790
You have my word.
You both do.

06:35.790 --> 06:36.620
Okay.

06:42.330 --> 06:43.670
Is this Megan Hunt?

06:43.670 --> 06:44.830
Yeah.

06:44.830 --> 06:47.380
Nastiest abdominal wound
I've ever seen.

06:47.380 --> 06:49.830
Massive hernia,
giant fistula.

06:49.830 --> 06:53.170
The abdominal layers have
scarred and fused to each other.

06:53.170 --> 06:55.330
Her small bowel and colon
are just --

06:55.330 --> 06:57.000
One big blob.

06:57.000 --> 06:58.580
And there's not enough
healthy skin

06:58.580 --> 07:00.330
to properly
close the wound.

07:00.330 --> 07:01.920
I think we just
optimize her nutrition,

07:01.920 --> 07:03.210
vac the wound, and wait.

07:03.210 --> 07:04.960
I mean,
it'll close eventually.

07:04.960 --> 07:07.710
She wants us
to reverse the colostomy.

07:07.710 --> 07:09.880
I can't see a way
to make that happen.

07:09.880 --> 07:11.620
Well, I can.

07:11.620 --> 07:12.750
And you taught it to me.

07:17.250 --> 07:20.580
So, I would like to
reapproximate the abdominal wall

07:20.580 --> 07:22.500
a little bit at a time.

07:22.500 --> 07:25.210
Put in tissue expanders
to stretch the skin

07:25.210 --> 07:27.540
and then pull the abdomen
back together slowly.

07:27.540 --> 07:29.080
And then we'll go back in,

07:29.080 --> 07:32.040
take down the fistula,
reverse the colostomy,

07:32.040 --> 07:34.830
and I'll close with
a component separation surgery.

07:34.830 --> 07:36.040
Which means what?

07:36.040 --> 07:38.120
Which means
she's my new favorite person.

07:38.120 --> 07:40.620
Who are you?
I'm Meredith Grey.

07:40.620 --> 07:42.710
Thank you for your service,
Dr. Hunt.

07:42.710 --> 07:45.040
Well, I admit I've been
out of the O.R. for a while,

07:45.040 --> 07:47.330
but this sounds like
a risky surgery.

07:47.330 --> 07:49.000
Bailey:
It most definitely is.

07:49.000 --> 07:50.830
And there's no guarantee
that it'll work.

07:50.830 --> 07:52.670
Yeah, which is why
Dr. Bailey and I

07:52.670 --> 07:55.790
would recommend
a more conservative approach.

07:55.790 --> 07:58.040
Thank you, but I just came back
from being presumed dead.

07:58.040 --> 08:00.120
I'm not about to
play it safe.

08:02.290 --> 08:04.830
Also, it's really hard

08:04.830 --> 08:07.420
to live with an open
abdominal wound in Iraq.

08:07.420 --> 08:08.750
What do you mean,
"in Iraq"?

08:08.750 --> 08:10.420
[ Sighs ]

08:10.420 --> 08:13.120
Yeah, I was trying to figure out
how to tell you this.

08:13.120 --> 08:15.540
As soon as I'm well,
I have to go back to Iraq.

08:17.790 --> 08:19.500
My child is there.

08:19.500 --> 08:26.500
♪♪

08:33.880 --> 08:35.080
His name is Farouk. His parents
were Syrian insurgent fighters.

08:35.080 --> 08:36.920
They both died in combat.

08:36.920 --> 08:40.120
I took him in when he was 4.
He's 10 now.

08:40.120 --> 08:41.830
I'm the only parent he has,

08:41.830 --> 08:44.790
and he is the main reason that
I stayed sane all these years.

08:44.790 --> 08:46.120
I'm a grandmother?

08:46.120 --> 08:47.500
[ Laughs ]

08:47.500 --> 08:48.920
And you couldn't
bring him with you?

08:48.920 --> 08:50.380
You're
a national hero.

08:50.380 --> 08:53.790
Tell that to
the U.S. immigration laws.

08:53.790 --> 08:57.000
If your surgery works,
I'll have a functioning bowel?

08:57.000 --> 08:58.170
That's the plan.

08:58.170 --> 08:59.620
Then that's
what we're doing.

09:04.420 --> 09:08.040
[ Woman speaking indistinctly
on P.A. ]

09:08.040 --> 09:09.960
Meredith?

09:09.960 --> 09:11.540
I'm sorry --
I would never have asked you

09:11.540 --> 09:13.250
to consult
on Megan's case.

09:13.250 --> 09:14.880
Oh, you didn't ask me.

09:14.880 --> 09:18.420
Well, is you working on Megan
the best idea?

09:18.420 --> 09:20.380
I mean, family and all,
conflict of interest.

09:20.380 --> 09:22.670
She's not my family.

09:22.670 --> 09:24.380
[ Hushed voice ]
Well, I get that, but...

09:24.380 --> 09:26.210
I am the best person
for this job.

09:26.210 --> 09:27.380
Just let me help.

09:30.080 --> 09:33.080
[ Woman speaking indistinctly
on P.A. ]

09:35.210 --> 09:37.290
Are you crying
about the empty board?

09:37.290 --> 09:39.710
Did you see Steph
last night?

09:39.710 --> 09:41.540
Oh. um, yeah.

09:41.540 --> 09:42.620
Yeah, look, we --

09:42.620 --> 09:45.250
She was hurt,
but we got to her in time.

09:45.250 --> 09:48.670
It was kind of unbelievable.
I mean, it was, uh...

09:48.670 --> 09:50.790
It was thrilling,
actually.

09:50.790 --> 09:53.120
You know?
It was a rush.

09:53.120 --> 09:54.380
Who am I
gonna talk to now?

09:54.380 --> 09:56.710
Who am I gonna
compete against?

09:56.710 --> 09:58.710
W-Who's gonna tell me
when I'm being ridiculous

09:58.710 --> 10:01.330
or -- or when I stink
and need a shower?

10:01.330 --> 10:03.380
Way to make Stephanie's
life-changing
injuries about you.

10:03.380 --> 10:05.670
You called it a rush!

10:07.670 --> 10:08.830
Yeah, I guess.

10:08.830 --> 10:10.380
Oh, and, uh, you do.

10:10.380 --> 10:11.460
Do what?

10:11.460 --> 10:12.790
Need a shower.

10:12.790 --> 10:14.710
[ Scoffs ]

10:14.710 --> 10:16.710
-Hey.
-Oh. Hey.

10:16.710 --> 10:18.000
You busy?

10:18.000 --> 10:20.540
Uh,
have you seen the board?

10:20.540 --> 10:21.790
Come with me.

10:27.880 --> 10:29.830
Hey, looking good, Max.

10:29.830 --> 10:31.540
Feeling good, Dr. Alex.

10:31.540 --> 10:33.380
Hey, Max, this is,
uh, Dr. Wilson.
Hi.

10:33.380 --> 10:36.330
She's gonna read me
your chart, okay?

10:36.330 --> 10:38.960
Max Spencer,
7 years old.

10:38.960 --> 10:42.120
Has had intermittent abdominal
pain and vomiting for months.

10:42.120 --> 10:44.080
Upper GI found
evidence of malrotation

10:44.080 --> 10:46.120
due to the presence
of bands.

10:46.120 --> 10:49.460
Needs a Ladd's procedure,
which is scheduled for --

10:49.460 --> 10:52.620
As soon my gastric emptying
study comes back normal.

10:52.620 --> 10:54.420
[ Laughs ] Exactly.

10:54.420 --> 10:56.040
Wow.
You're pretty smart, huh?

10:57.830 --> 11:01.960
♪♪

11:01.960 --> 11:02.920
Look!

11:04.290 --> 11:06.830
Allora the Warrior Queen!
Is that you?!

11:09.210 --> 11:11.080
Max, don't blow
her cover.

11:12.380 --> 11:13.960
She's gonna be
doing your surgery.

11:13.960 --> 11:19.580
♪♪

11:19.580 --> 11:21.710
Uh --

11:21.710 --> 11:23.620
Are you serious?

11:23.620 --> 11:26.710
You're gonna let me do
a Ladd's procedure? By myself?

11:26.710 --> 11:28.120
Think you can handle it?

11:28.120 --> 11:30.420
Handle it?
I'm a frickin' warrior queen!

11:30.420 --> 11:32.080
[ Chuckles ]

11:34.000 --> 11:36.670
♪♪

11:36.670 --> 11:40.710
[ Cellphones buzzing, chiming ]

11:40.710 --> 11:42.540
-You paged?
-Sub-I's.

11:42.540 --> 11:44.500
[ Clears throat ] What?

11:44.500 --> 11:46.580
As if we didn't have
enough to deal with today,

11:46.580 --> 11:48.210
Minnick's new sub-I's
are here.

11:48.210 --> 11:50.960
-Sub-I's?
-The sub-interns.

11:50.960 --> 11:53.420
The group of
fourth-year med students

11:53.420 --> 11:55.210
she's been courting
to be potential interns?

11:56.540 --> 11:58.380
They're here
for a six-week rotation.

11:58.380 --> 12:00.080
She didn't talk to you
about this?

12:00.080 --> 12:02.080
Well, she may have
mentioned it,

12:02.080 --> 12:03.500
but I got pretty good
at ignoring her.

12:03.500 --> 12:06.290
[ Scoffs ] Well, they're here.
And they're yours.

12:06.290 --> 12:09.380
And they're all in the top 10%
of their programs.

12:09.380 --> 12:11.460
So they're completely
socially inept?

12:11.460 --> 12:12.880
Probably.

12:12.880 --> 12:15.000
[ Grumbles ]

12:17.170 --> 12:18.330
[ Knock on door ]
[ Cellphone chimes ]

12:18.330 --> 12:19.710
Dr. Hunt.

12:19.710 --> 12:22.500
-Fistulagram?
-Exactly.

12:22.500 --> 12:24.580
Are you sure you want to put
yourself through all this?

12:24.580 --> 12:26.670
It's a tube in my belly,
with some dye.

12:26.670 --> 12:27.960
This is nothing.

12:27.960 --> 12:29.790
Well, I don't
need to see it.
[ Chuckles ]

12:29.790 --> 12:32.170
I'll be back tomorrow
bright and early, sweetheart.

12:32.170 --> 12:33.420
[ Door closes ]

12:33.420 --> 12:35.460
You don't get to
see this, either.

12:35.460 --> 12:38.080
-Yeah, I'll take your mom home.
-Okay.

12:38.080 --> 12:39.420
[ Chuckles ]

12:39.420 --> 12:41.170
-Goodbye, Meredith.
-Goodbye, Evelyn.

12:49.250 --> 12:51.380
So, you and my mom
are on a first-name basis?

12:51.380 --> 12:54.960
Well, I was in both of
Owen's weddings, so...

12:54.960 --> 12:56.420
Both of them?

12:56.420 --> 12:57.580
Ho-ho-ho.

12:57.580 --> 13:00.080
This is exciting.
Give me the scoop.

13:00.080 --> 13:02.380
Which of Owen wives
did you like better, and why?

13:02.380 --> 13:04.250
I couldn't possibly
answer that question.

13:05.460 --> 13:06.790
Ugh. Fine.

13:06.790 --> 13:09.710
Don't talk about Owen.
Talk about Nathan.

13:09.710 --> 13:12.420
Who was he dating, when,
and for how long?

13:12.420 --> 13:15.170
Okay, Megan,
will you let Dr. Grey

13:15.170 --> 13:16.540
just focus
on her job, please?

13:16.540 --> 13:18.000
-Buzzkill.
-[ Chuckles ]

13:19.790 --> 13:21.540
Take a deep breath.

13:21.540 --> 13:23.790
All right.
Uh, here is the ER.

13:23.790 --> 13:25.710
We are entering
the ER.

13:25.710 --> 13:28.330
As you probably know, we are
a level-one trauma center.

13:28.330 --> 13:29.830
We are a level-one
trauma center.

13:29.830 --> 13:32.670
Dr. Webber, what is the
trauma volume for Grey Sloan?

13:32.670 --> 13:36.120
Okay, the ER sees
120,000 cases a year.
The ER sees
120,000 cases a year.

13:36.120 --> 13:38.500
Of which 5,000 are...
5,000...

13:38.500 --> 13:40.000
...related to trauma.
...are related to trauma.

13:40.000 --> 13:42.750
22% -- penetrating trauma.
22% -- penetrating trauma.

13:42.750 --> 13:44.960
Uh, your name, again?
Candace Warner.

13:44.960 --> 13:46.580
Uh, Candace, uh...

13:46.580 --> 13:48.830
it might be a good idea
to put away the phone.

13:48.830 --> 13:50.120
I find
the voice-to-notes app

13:50.120 --> 13:51.920
the most efficient way
to record the tour.

13:51.920 --> 13:54.500
And I find it the most annoying
way for you to do the tour.

13:54.500 --> 13:55.920
[ Doors open ]
Ben: Coming through!

13:55.920 --> 13:57.880
Oh! Okay.
What do you got?

13:57.880 --> 13:59.380
Pedestrian versus SUV.

13:59.380 --> 14:01.420
Multiple open fractures.
Arrested en route.

14:01.420 --> 14:03.420
April: Let's get set up
for an ED thoracotomy.

14:03.420 --> 14:04.500
Mind if we observe?

14:04.500 --> 14:06.120
Long as you stay
out of my way!

14:06.120 --> 14:09.210
Chest tray,
size 6 1/2 gloves.

14:09.210 --> 14:12.000
Ready? On my count.
One, two, three.

14:12.000 --> 14:14.080
Glove me.
Betadine his chest.

14:14.080 --> 14:16.120
Someone take over bagging.

14:16.120 --> 14:17.080
All right.

14:17.080 --> 14:19.420
Hey, Candace,
if you were busy

14:19.420 --> 14:21.040
dictating all of this
into your mobile device,

14:21.040 --> 14:22.580
you'd miss all of the --

14:22.580 --> 14:24.170
Aaaaaaahhh!

14:24.170 --> 14:26.960
Aaaaaaaaaaaaaaaahhhhhhh!

14:26.960 --> 14:29.120
-Aaaahh!
-Dr. Webber?

14:29.120 --> 14:30.580
Okay, look, everybody out!
Let's go!

14:30.580 --> 14:32.790
Everybody out! Out, out!
Everybody out!
Aaaaaah!

14:32.790 --> 14:35.170
-Aaaaaaaaahhhh!
-Get him up.

14:35.170 --> 14:36.830
He's 35?

14:36.830 --> 14:38.580
Maybe now he's 38.

14:38.580 --> 14:40.620
-And a fireman?
-Mm-hmm.

14:40.620 --> 14:42.250
Oh, ho ho!

14:42.250 --> 14:43.290
Get it, Mom.

14:43.290 --> 14:44.380
[ Both laugh ]

14:44.380 --> 14:46.170
You know, I didn't
like it at first.

14:46.170 --> 14:47.580
Yeah,
I still don't like it.

14:47.580 --> 14:49.210
But it makes her happy,
so...

14:49.210 --> 14:51.080
[ Laughs ]

14:54.080 --> 14:55.790
I never should've stopped
looking for you.

14:55.790 --> 14:56.960
Ohh.

14:58.790 --> 15:00.620
Owen, look at me.

15:00.620 --> 15:02.380
I'm okay.

15:02.380 --> 15:04.670
There were some beatings
in the beginning

15:04.670 --> 15:06.420
to make sure
I didn't try to escape.

15:06.420 --> 15:09.460
But after a while, I made
friends and played cards

15:09.460 --> 15:12.170
and did surgery
and raised my kid,
and I was okay.

15:12.170 --> 15:14.750
I didn't want you to waste
your life looking for me.

15:14.750 --> 15:17.880
I used to pray every night
that you had gone home to Mom

15:17.880 --> 15:19.500
and married anyone but Beth.

15:19.500 --> 15:21.580
[ Chuckles ]

15:21.580 --> 15:23.880
I wanted you to be happy.

15:23.880 --> 15:26.420
I still want you
to be happy.

15:26.420 --> 15:29.580
And this guilt, it's --
it's worse than useless.

15:31.710 --> 15:33.960
And...there's something
I really need you to do.

15:33.960 --> 15:35.750
Anything.

15:35.750 --> 15:37.920
When I eat, it comes out through
the fistula, like, instantly.

15:37.920 --> 15:39.620
It's disgusting.

15:39.620 --> 15:41.330
So I'm gonna need you
to get me an ice-blended mocha

15:41.330 --> 15:42.580
while Nathan's
driving Mom home.

15:42.580 --> 15:44.120
Are you serious?

15:44.120 --> 15:47.120
Ice-blended mocha, stat.
Extra whipped cream.

15:47.120 --> 15:49.000
[ Knock on door ]
Eliza?

15:49.000 --> 15:50.460
Hey, come on. Come on.

15:50.460 --> 15:52.460
I've given you
all the time that I can.

15:52.460 --> 15:55.620
Now you -- you have to let me
help you lick your wounds.

15:58.960 --> 16:00.670
Wow.

16:00.670 --> 16:03.000
That sounded dirtier
than I meant it to.

16:04.670 --> 16:07.580
Eliza! Come on.

16:07.580 --> 16:15.620
♪♪

16:15.620 --> 16:23.920
♪♪

16:23.920 --> 16:27.500
[ Indistinct conversations ]

16:27.500 --> 16:31.460
Coffee after 5:00 p.m.? You are
never gonna sleep tonight.

16:32.830 --> 16:33.960
Teddy?

16:33.960 --> 16:35.790
-Hi!
-Teddy!

16:35.790 --> 16:38.000
-What are you doing here?
-Well, Megan's home.

16:38.000 --> 16:39.750
You didn't think I'd come
and see how you're doing?

16:39.750 --> 16:42.210
[ Both laugh ]

16:50.000 --> 16:52.210
[ Ship horn blows ]

16:52.210 --> 16:54.250
[ Pounding, drill whirring ]

16:54.250 --> 16:57.710
[ Indistinct talking ]

16:57.710 --> 16:59.710
Ben:
So, what's going on here?

16:59.710 --> 17:02.380
It's hard to say.
We're still in pre-op.

17:02.380 --> 17:04.880
Yeah, I'm pretty sure
that's the lead surgeon.

17:04.880 --> 17:07.250
-Yeah.
-Oh, and that over there?

17:07.250 --> 17:09.500
Yeah, I think that's
his best scrub nurse.

17:09.500 --> 17:11.330
Huh.

17:13.040 --> 17:15.380
-Is he hot?
-Well, he's not un-hot.

17:15.380 --> 17:17.080
But it's only been
a few dates, so...

17:17.080 --> 17:18.920
-[ Laughing ] Ow!
-Sorry.

17:18.920 --> 17:21.750
Just a few more of these shots
to relax the oblique muscles,

17:21.750 --> 17:23.580
create a little more laxity.

17:23.580 --> 17:25.250
Yeah, well,
when you're done with that,

17:25.250 --> 17:27.120
you think you can put a little
of that Botox right there?

17:27.120 --> 17:28.580
[ Laughter ]

17:28.580 --> 17:30.540
That brow has not unfurrowed
since I got home.

17:30.540 --> 17:31.920
Well, it's a brother's job
to worry.

17:31.920 --> 17:33.330
-Thank you.
-Wrong!

17:33.330 --> 17:34.670
It is a mother's job
to worry.

17:34.670 --> 17:36.380
It is a brother's job
to entertain.

17:36.380 --> 17:37.960
Oh, so you want me
to tap dance or...?

17:37.960 --> 17:40.210
No, but if you could dig out
the kilt and bagpipes...
Ohh.

17:40.210 --> 17:41.750
...that would definitely
make me feel better.

17:41.750 --> 17:43.080
Okay, you play
the bagpipes?

17:43.080 --> 17:45.290
For one summer
in the eighth grade,

17:45.290 --> 17:46.380
and she'll never let me
live it down!

17:46.380 --> 17:48.250
Oh, my God! I want
to see that so badly.

17:48.250 --> 17:49.580
Me too. Look.
Can I turn around now?

17:49.580 --> 17:51.120
All: No!

17:51.120 --> 17:53.250
Avery.
You almost done here?

17:53.250 --> 17:55.080
I-I'm doing
a tumor board presentation,

17:55.080 --> 17:57.000
and it's kind of pointless
without you there.

17:57.000 --> 17:59.040
Amelia, this is Teddy.
She came all the way from --

17:59.040 --> 18:01.040
From Germany, right.
Um, we spoke on the phone.

18:01.040 --> 18:02.960
-Yeah. It's so nice to meet --
-Yes, yeah, good to meet you.

18:02.960 --> 18:05.540
Um...I'm sorry.
I'm distracted.

18:05.540 --> 18:07.620
I have a kid
with an osteoblastoma, so...

18:07.620 --> 18:09.330
You're presenting him.
I totally get it.

18:09.330 --> 18:10.960
Jackson: You know what?
I'm done here.

18:10.960 --> 18:12.580
I'll just check
back in on you later.

18:12.580 --> 18:14.330
No straining those abdominal
muscles, please, okay?

18:14.330 --> 18:15.120
Yes, sir.

18:19.920 --> 18:21.540
[ Door closes ]

18:21.540 --> 18:23.420
What?

18:23.420 --> 18:25.380
I've been meaning to ask.

18:25.380 --> 18:26.540
How's married life?

18:28.960 --> 18:32.580
[ Chuckles softly ]

18:32.580 --> 18:34.380
How's your colostomy bag?

18:34.380 --> 18:36.750
[ Laughs ]

18:36.750 --> 18:41.000
Our patient is a 14-year-old
in constant and increasing pain.

18:41.000 --> 18:42.540
DeLuca?

18:42.540 --> 18:45.040
On MRI, he was found to have
a large osteoblastoma

18:45.040 --> 18:47.580
involving the temporal bone,
the mandible, and the mastoid.

18:47.580 --> 18:50.040
It encases the 7th and 8th
cranial nerves.

18:50.040 --> 18:52.420
We managed to obtain a biopsy
through the ear,

18:52.420 --> 18:53.580
and it is benign.

18:53.580 --> 18:55.920
I can resect it from
a sub-occipital approach,

18:55.920 --> 18:57.880
but I will need assistance
with a jaw reconstruction

18:57.880 --> 18:59.330
and temporalis
muscle flap.

18:59.330 --> 19:01.000
That tumor's inoperable.

19:01.000 --> 19:04.500
I'm not a big believer
in inoperable.

19:04.500 --> 19:08.080
God, yes. Unicorns, possibly.
Inoperable, no.

19:08.080 --> 19:10.120
Then start hunting unicorns.
Your chances are better.

19:10.120 --> 19:11.960
You don't hunt unicorns.
What's the matter with you?

19:11.960 --> 19:12.830
You should treat it
with radiation.

19:12.830 --> 19:14.580
Which won't help much.

19:14.580 --> 19:16.330
If you go in, you'll cut
the cranial nerves.
No, I won't.

19:16.330 --> 19:18.040
You try to resect
along the zygomatic arch,

19:18.040 --> 19:19.540
you could send this kid home
with no lower jaw.

19:19.540 --> 19:21.380
What, so we just
send him home to die?

19:21.380 --> 19:23.420
No. You don't send him
home to die. You --

19:23.420 --> 19:24.830
Send him home to
suffer in miserable pain

19:24.830 --> 19:26.250
for the rest of his
miserable life.

19:26.250 --> 19:27.710
I was gonna say send him
to a pain clinic.

19:27.710 --> 19:29.210
Mine is more accurate.

19:31.620 --> 19:33.750
He's letting you do
a pediatric Ladd's procedure?

19:33.750 --> 19:35.790
Like, the whole thing?
Solo?

19:35.790 --> 19:37.170
[ Inhales sharply ]

19:37.170 --> 19:39.920
Is that a bad reason to fall
back in love with someone?

19:39.920 --> 19:42.420
[ Scoffs ] Seems as good
a reason as any to me.

19:42.420 --> 19:46.210
Mm...it's a bad idea.
Like, bad bad.

19:46.210 --> 19:48.170
Like "it ends
with ruined lives

19:48.170 --> 19:49.880
and someone
going to prison" bad.

19:49.880 --> 19:52.210
-It's --
-No.

19:52.210 --> 19:54.500
-[ Clears throat ]
-"No," what?

19:54.500 --> 19:56.460
No, I will not be
your new Stephanie.

19:56.460 --> 19:58.750
Y-- She had way more patience
for all of your --

19:58.750 --> 20:00.210
Yeah, no. No.

20:00.210 --> 20:04.960
All right,
and this is the skills lab.

20:04.960 --> 20:08.080
Uh, Dr. Wilson, have you met
our new sub-interns?

20:08.080 --> 20:10.500
I...didn't know
that was a thing.

20:10.500 --> 20:11.710
[ Chuckles ]
Hm.

20:11.710 --> 20:14.580
This is Dr. Wilson.
She's a senior resident.

20:14.580 --> 20:16.790
You want to show the kids
what you're working on, Wilson?

20:16.790 --> 20:20.830
Yes. Uh, well, this is
a virtual dissection table.

20:20.830 --> 20:22.880
So, for this case...
[ Cellphones clicking ]

20:22.880 --> 20:25.330
...I'm going to
lift the omentum

20:25.330 --> 20:27.380
and then run the bowel
from the ligament of Treitz

20:27.380 --> 20:30.880
to the ileocecal...
valve.

20:30.880 --> 20:32.210
[ Clicking continues ]

20:32.210 --> 20:33.330
Look up from your notes,
people!

20:34.710 --> 20:35.750
Sir, if I may,
this is why --

20:35.750 --> 20:36.880
No, you may not.

20:36.880 --> 20:40.000
♪♪

20:40.000 --> 20:43.620
♪ Can't keep my hands
to myself ♪

20:43.620 --> 20:45.080
She ghosted you.

20:45.080 --> 20:46.380
What? What's that?

20:46.380 --> 20:48.960
No text? No note?
Just disappeared?

20:48.960 --> 20:50.210
She ghosted you.

20:51.960 --> 20:53.580
People do that?

20:53.580 --> 20:55.420
Like, often enough
that it has its own term?

20:55.420 --> 20:56.710
It's cruel and awful,

20:56.710 --> 20:58.670
and no one should do it
to anyone ever, and...

20:58.670 --> 21:00.120
I am so sorry.

21:00.120 --> 21:04.000
♪ Might be over now,
but I feel it still ♪

21:04.000 --> 21:06.250
Well, at least she
was crystal-clear
about her intentions.

21:06.250 --> 21:08.330
She didn't confuse you with
a whole Montana situation

21:08.330 --> 21:09.540
and then just...linger.

21:09.540 --> 21:11.250
What's a Montana situation?

21:11.250 --> 21:13.040
Is that another term
that I've never heard of?

21:13.040 --> 21:15.000
I feel so old.

21:16.420 --> 21:17.790
Surprise.

21:17.790 --> 21:19.000
[ Gasps ]
Oh, my God!

21:19.000 --> 21:20.790
Oh my God! You're here!

21:20.790 --> 21:23.500
Callie left me, and she went
to New York, and she took Sofia,

21:23.500 --> 21:25.170
and I managed to find love
again, but then she got fired,

21:25.170 --> 21:26.790
and I've been meaning
to call you forever,
and I'm so sorry.

21:26.790 --> 21:29.000
Did I ghost you? 'Cause I'm --
I'm -- I'm so sorry.

21:29.000 --> 21:31.120
I'm a terrible friend,
and I'm so glad you're here!

21:31.120 --> 21:32.880
[ Both laugh ]

21:32.880 --> 21:34.460
♪ I been feeling it
since 1966 ♪

21:34.460 --> 21:35.420
Hey.

21:37.000 --> 21:39.120
What? I got something
on my face?

21:39.120 --> 21:41.670
No. No, your face
is perfect.

21:42.750 --> 21:44.170
I mean...

21:44.170 --> 21:46.250
I...have to --
I have a --

21:46.250 --> 21:47.330
What's that?

21:47.330 --> 21:50.210
This was great,
but I have, uh...

21:50.210 --> 21:51.750
[ Clears throat ]

21:54.620 --> 21:57.580
♪ Ooh-ooh, I'm a rebel
just for kicks, now ♪

21:57.580 --> 22:00.710
♪ I been feelin' it
since 1986, now ♪

22:00.710 --> 22:03.670
♪ Might be over now,
but I feel it still ♪

22:03.670 --> 22:04.790
Can you hear me?

22:04.790 --> 22:07.210
Yeah.

22:07.210 --> 22:09.120
I don't think
you should be up there.

22:09.120 --> 22:10.750
Why not?

22:10.750 --> 22:12.750
Because what you are about to
see is decidedly unsexy.

22:12.750 --> 22:14.960
Blood...guts.

22:14.960 --> 22:16.420
Nah, you look good
in anything.

22:16.420 --> 22:17.960
[ Laughing ] Shut up.

22:19.380 --> 22:21.460
-Hi.
-Hi.

22:21.460 --> 22:23.210
Do you have any questions
before we get started?

22:23.210 --> 22:25.380
-Can I see the expanders?
-Of course.

22:25.380 --> 22:27.460
Bokhee?

22:27.460 --> 22:30.620
Wow! That is --
Wow. That's big.

22:30.620 --> 22:32.670
We'll deflate them
to put them in,

22:32.670 --> 22:34.920
and then we will slowly
reinflate them with saline.

22:34.920 --> 22:36.790
We're gonna need as much space
as we can get.

22:36.790 --> 22:38.170
You know what we'd say
in the Army right now?

22:38.170 --> 22:39.250
What?

22:39.250 --> 22:41.540
-Say it with me, Nathan!
-Mm.

22:41.540 --> 22:42.880
-Hooah!
-Hooah!

22:42.880 --> 22:43.830
-Hooah!
-Hooah!

22:43.830 --> 22:46.210
-Hooah!
-Hooah!

22:46.210 --> 22:47.500
Let's do this thing,
Dr. Grey.

22:47.500 --> 22:48.540
Let's do it.

22:48.540 --> 22:49.790
Okay.

22:49.790 --> 22:51.880
[ Monitor beeping ]

22:54.880 --> 22:57.040
[ Woman speaking indistinctly
on P.A. ]

22:57.040 --> 22:59.120
[ Indistinct conversations ]

23:01.830 --> 23:06.000
[ Hyperventilating ]

23:06.000 --> 23:07.380
Okay, all right.

23:07.380 --> 23:08.830
Okay.

23:08.830 --> 23:11.080
All right. Look. Hey.

23:11.080 --> 23:13.790
This is a minor surgery.
She'll be fine.

23:13.790 --> 23:15.670
This stage is nothing.

23:15.670 --> 23:17.330
[ Breathing rapidly ]

23:17.330 --> 23:18.670
All right.
You know what?

23:18.670 --> 23:20.540
You -- You need to put your head
between your knees.

23:20.540 --> 23:22.250
No.

23:22.250 --> 23:23.500
Head between your knees,
Major!

23:25.380 --> 23:26.920
Sit down.

23:26.920 --> 23:29.460
[ Breathing rapidly ]

23:29.460 --> 23:32.120
All right. That's it.
All right. Breathe.

23:34.250 --> 23:36.880
I can't lose her
again, Teddy.

23:36.880 --> 23:38.040
I know.

23:38.040 --> 23:39.580
I lost 10 years.

23:39.580 --> 23:41.120
She doesn't even look
the way I remember her.

23:41.120 --> 23:43.790
I lost her
even in my memory.

23:43.790 --> 23:47.210
And now she's back.

23:47.210 --> 23:49.000
And I can't
lose her again.

23:49.000 --> 23:50.790
I know. It's okay.

23:52.210 --> 23:54.750
Listen, you have
a plane to catch.

23:54.750 --> 23:56.330
I'm not going anywhere.

23:59.120 --> 24:00.960
[ Breathing slowly ]

24:00.960 --> 24:05.290
♪♪

24:13.830 --> 24:15.710
[ Pounding, drills whirring ]

24:17.250 --> 24:19.170
[ Indistinct talking ]

24:23.330 --> 24:25.750
Ortho docs?

24:25.750 --> 24:27.080
Bailey: Only louder!

24:27.080 --> 24:29.540
[ Pounding, whirring continue ]

24:29.540 --> 24:32.580
Meredith: Okay, you're
gonna feel a little pinch.

24:32.580 --> 24:34.330
It shouldn't hurt
that bad, okay?

24:34.330 --> 24:35.710
That's it.

24:35.710 --> 24:37.000
You good?

24:37.000 --> 24:38.420
Mm-hmm.

24:38.420 --> 24:40.250
Meredith, I was so sorry
to hear about Derek.

24:40.250 --> 24:42.750
Oh. Thanks.
Me too.

24:42.750 --> 24:43.790
Who's Derek?

24:45.040 --> 24:47.750
I-It's a long story.

24:47.750 --> 24:49.830
[ Cellphone chimes ]

24:49.830 --> 24:51.290
Oh.

24:51.290 --> 24:53.750
This is for you.

24:53.750 --> 24:55.830
[ Gasps ] It's Farouk!

24:55.830 --> 24:57.500
Mm.

24:57.500 --> 24:59.000
He's a selfie master.

24:59.000 --> 25:00.210
[ Laughter ]

25:00.210 --> 25:01.710
That's an
impressive snout.

25:01.710 --> 25:04.080
-Yeah, excellent work.
-Where is he now?

25:04.080 --> 25:07.380
Ah, he's with U.S. Military
in Baghdad.

25:07.380 --> 25:09.120
I haven't been able
to legally adopt him,

25:09.120 --> 25:11.620
and he's a Syrian refugee.

25:11.620 --> 25:13.290
It'll take years before
I can get him here, if ever.

25:13.290 --> 25:15.210
I just want
to get back to him.

25:16.420 --> 25:18.000
Hey, Nathan, are you
planning on moving with --

25:18.000 --> 25:19.920
Megan, uh, looks like
you could use some air.

25:19.920 --> 25:21.380
Meredith, is it okay
if we take her outside?

25:21.380 --> 25:24.120
Oh, my God. Outside?
Yes, please.

25:24.120 --> 25:26.420
-I got it! [ Laughs ]
-You all right?

25:26.420 --> 25:28.920
So this is what it
feels like to be a robot.

25:28.920 --> 25:30.670
[ Both laugh ]

25:30.670 --> 25:33.040
I don't know about robot.
I'm thinking more...alien?

25:33.040 --> 25:35.210
You think? Or, like,
strange sea creature, maybe?

25:35.210 --> 25:36.210
[ Shrieking ]

25:36.210 --> 25:37.750
There you go.
That's it. That's it.

25:37.750 --> 25:40.170
[ Shrieking continues]
[ Laughs ]

25:40.170 --> 25:42.080
You got a little weird
when I asked

25:42.080 --> 25:44.040
about Nathan
moving with Megan.

25:44.040 --> 25:45.080
You still upset
with him?

25:47.790 --> 25:49.750
Nathan and Meredith
were a thing.

25:49.750 --> 25:52.080
Right up until we got
the call about Megan.

25:52.080 --> 25:54.120
And we don't want her
to know.

25:55.420 --> 25:57.580
Wait. Are you --
Are you kidding?

25:57.580 --> 25:58.580
Owen, are you kidding me?

26:00.460 --> 26:03.330
Meredith is Megan's surgeon,
and you don't want her to know?

26:06.290 --> 26:07.710
You ready?

26:07.710 --> 26:10.120
Okay, you're gonna
go to sleep now.

26:10.120 --> 26:12.120
When you wake up,
you're gonna be...

26:12.120 --> 26:13.670
A warrior king!

26:13.670 --> 26:15.540
[ Laughs ] Exactly!

26:15.540 --> 26:16.580
Okay.

26:16.580 --> 26:18.250
[ Monitor beeping ]

26:18.250 --> 26:20.830
All right.
You're gonna do great, Max.

26:20.830 --> 26:23.000
[ Door opens ]

26:23.000 --> 26:25.580
Richard:
And this is the O.R.

26:25.580 --> 26:27.880
Dr. Karev,
mind if we observe?

26:27.880 --> 26:29.210
Um...

26:29.210 --> 26:31.420
It's up to you.
It's your case.

26:31.420 --> 26:32.420
It's fine.

26:32.420 --> 26:33.620
Let's scrub.

26:33.620 --> 26:36.540
Okay, great. Let's go.

26:36.540 --> 26:38.120
Hey. Meredith?

26:38.120 --> 26:39.290
Meredith,
you have a minute?

26:39.290 --> 26:40.290
Hi. Yeah.

26:40.290 --> 26:41.620
Did you read this article

26:41.620 --> 26:43.920
that Cristina published
on ex vivo lung perfusion?

26:43.920 --> 26:45.580
It's --
It's not appropriate.

26:45.580 --> 26:47.580
To read
Cristina's article?

26:47.580 --> 26:49.540
No, for you to operate
on Megan Hunt.

26:49.540 --> 26:52.580
Oh. She chose the surgery.
She's aware of the risks.

26:52.580 --> 26:54.830
But she doesn't know about
your history with her fiancé.

26:54.830 --> 26:56.420
I mean, that's a serious
conflict of interest.

26:56.420 --> 26:58.420
You have to step away
from this case.

26:58.420 --> 26:59.880
Well, I --
You don't get to
talk to her like that.

26:59.880 --> 27:01.210
-Amelia.
-Excuse me?

27:01.210 --> 27:03.170
Okay, you're not
Megan's doctor,
Amelia.

27:03.170 --> 27:05.500
so if Meredith has decided
that she is equipped
to handle a surgery,

27:05.500 --> 27:07.710
you don't get to
just show up here...
I can fight
my own battles.

27:07.710 --> 27:09.250
...like you own the place
and talk to her like that.

27:09.250 --> 27:10.420
I shouldn't have to.

27:10.420 --> 27:12.920
Megan is Owen's sister,
and you're Owen's wife,

27:12.920 --> 27:15.040
so I shouldn't have to
advocate for Megan and Owen,

27:15.040 --> 27:16.580
who have been through
hell and back --

27:16.580 --> 27:18.290
a hell which I've
personally witnessed.

27:18.290 --> 27:20.080
I shouldn't have to show up here
and advocate for them,

27:20.080 --> 27:21.500
because that's your job.

27:21.500 --> 27:23.620
But you're not doing it.
I have barely seen you.

27:23.620 --> 27:24.750
Because I have a patient.

27:24.750 --> 27:25.960
You also have a husband.

27:25.960 --> 27:28.620
I'm sorry. Is it 1952?

27:28.620 --> 27:31.290
Should I put on my apron
and mix him a gin and tonic?

27:31.290 --> 27:33.290
All right.

27:33.290 --> 27:36.040
It's not appropriate for you
to be Megan Hunt's surgeon --

27:36.040 --> 27:38.170
not when she doesn't have
the whole history.

27:40.670 --> 27:41.880
Who is she?

27:41.880 --> 27:45.460
That's...
Owen's...person.

27:45.460 --> 27:46.710
I have a patient.

27:51.540 --> 27:52.830
Bovie.

27:52.830 --> 27:54.120
[ Exhales sharply ] Wow.

27:54.120 --> 27:55.790
That's more bands
than I expected.

27:55.790 --> 27:57.670
Richard: Mind if we take
a closer look, Dr. Wilson?

27:57.670 --> 27:58.540
Be my guest.

27:58.540 --> 28:00.620
Okay.
Uh, not you, Candace.

28:00.620 --> 28:03.380
Oh, and not you, either.
Two at a time.

28:03.380 --> 28:05.920
I want you to see what
a malrotated bowel looks like.

28:05.920 --> 28:08.040
Alex: Normally the cecum
is in the right lower quadrant.

28:08.040 --> 28:09.710
Jo: But in this case,
there are abnormal fibrous bands

28:09.710 --> 28:11.170
in the right
upper quadrant,

28:11.170 --> 28:13.000
causing compressions
of the duodenum.

28:14.380 --> 28:16.040
-[ Gasps ]
-[ Gasps ]

28:17.580 --> 28:18.880
Levi: Oh, my God!

28:18.880 --> 28:20.580
-Richard: Oh, my God.
-Jo: Oh, my God!

28:20.580 --> 28:21.710
♪♪

28:28.380 --> 28:30.080
Alex: Step away
from the table, Wilson.

28:30.080 --> 28:32.120
Dr. Karev, my patient,
my surgery.

28:32.120 --> 28:33.420
Linda,
sponge stick, please.

28:33.420 --> 28:34.710
Okay.

28:38.750 --> 28:40.420
Jo: Okay, we're gonna
need to change out

28:40.420 --> 28:42.120
the contaminated instruments
for new ones.

28:42.120 --> 28:44.710
We'll need antibiotic solution,
several liters.

28:44.710 --> 28:47.000
And, Dr. Webber, please remove
your students from my O.R.

28:48.790 --> 28:51.000
If you...don't mind, sir.

28:51.000 --> 28:53.330
I-Indeed, Dr. Wilson.
Let's go. Out, out.

28:53.330 --> 28:55.170
Let's go.
Out, out, out! Out!

28:55.170 --> 28:57.330
-How's his pressure?
-Holding steady.

28:57.330 --> 28:59.330
Great.
Irrigation, please.

29:01.750 --> 29:03.880
You paged Avery?

29:03.880 --> 29:05.500
Yeah.
He's coming.

29:05.500 --> 29:06.830
When?

29:09.000 --> 29:10.710
Dr. Shepherd,
have you slept?

29:11.920 --> 29:15.670
Well, you stand in this room
staring at this tumor,

29:15.670 --> 29:19.620
and I don't see you eat,
I don't know when you sleep.

29:19.620 --> 29:21.500
Look, I made a promise
to this kid.

29:21.500 --> 29:23.330
And I made a promise
to his father.

29:25.120 --> 29:27.790
Also, my husband's sister
came back from the dead,

29:27.790 --> 29:29.210
and my brother didn't.

29:29.210 --> 29:31.420
So...sleep is not really
my thing right now.

29:31.420 --> 29:32.580
[ Door opens ]

29:32.580 --> 29:35.380
Avery. Good.

29:35.380 --> 29:38.000
I'm thinking
if we resect the tumor

29:38.000 --> 29:39.710
and reconstruct the jaw using
a portion of the temporal bone,

29:39.710 --> 29:41.000
we may be able
to get ahead of --

29:41.000 --> 29:43.120
This is
Kathleen Sampson.

29:43.120 --> 29:44.830
She was 17 when
this picture was taken.

29:44.830 --> 29:47.670
And this...
was her tumor.

29:47.670 --> 29:49.790
That look familiar?

29:49.790 --> 29:52.460
I did a sub-occipital approach
and a partial tumor resection,

29:52.460 --> 29:54.960
and then she looked...
like that.

29:54.960 --> 29:56.670
But she was still in pain.

29:56.670 --> 29:59.120
I hadn't gotten the whole thing,
so it began to grow back.

29:59.120 --> 30:02.170
So I had to go in
after it...again.

30:02.170 --> 30:04.790
Then again.

30:04.790 --> 30:06.540
You know what Kathleen
looks like now?

30:07.830 --> 30:09.250
There's Kathleen.

30:12.330 --> 30:14.120
I'm not taking
that boy's jaw apart.

30:15.830 --> 30:17.670
Please --
stop summoning me.

30:20.330 --> 30:22.000
[ Keys clacking ]

30:22.000 --> 30:23.500
[ Cellphone buzzing, chiming ]

30:23.500 --> 30:25.580
[ Woman speaking indistinctly
on P.A. ]

30:25.580 --> 30:27.750
-Dr. Webber?
-Ah. Karev.

30:27.750 --> 30:30.620
Uh, you know, I was
very impressed with
how Wilson handled --

30:30.620 --> 30:32.960
A situation she never should've
had to handle? Yeah, so was I.

30:32.960 --> 30:34.880
We're here to talk about
the sub-I's, Dr. Webber.

30:34.880 --> 30:36.380
The utterly inept...

30:36.380 --> 30:37.710
Bottom-of-the-barrel
med students

30:37.710 --> 30:39.170
you keep recklessly hauling
around the hospital.

30:41.250 --> 30:43.290
Oh, oh.

30:43.290 --> 30:46.000
So you two think you were
any better than them?

30:46.000 --> 30:49.620
Karev, you scraped in
by the skin of your teeth

30:49.620 --> 30:52.420
thanks to an essay you wrote
on testicular cancer --

30:52.420 --> 30:54.500
that I have since found
was a lie!

30:55.790 --> 30:59.330
Kepner, you failed your boards
and got fired --

30:59.330 --> 31:00.460
twice!

31:02.040 --> 31:03.920
I raised you two.

31:03.920 --> 31:06.500
I grew you into the surgeons
you are now.

31:06.500 --> 31:09.620
So you don't get to tell me
who I will and won't teach

31:09.620 --> 31:12.880
and how I should
or shouldn't do it!

31:12.880 --> 31:15.460
Now, I will thank you
to walk away.

31:15.460 --> 31:22.710
♪♪

31:22.710 --> 31:24.290
Minnick's sub-I's
can't be taught!

31:24.290 --> 31:26.290
They weren't meant
to be surgeons.

31:26.290 --> 31:27.710
I'm not sure they were
meant to be doctors.

31:27.710 --> 31:29.380
Maybe they can be
researchers in some lab,

31:29.380 --> 31:31.000
and even
that's questionable!

31:31.000 --> 31:34.710
♪♪

31:34.710 --> 31:37.210
Teddy, it is over
with Meredith, all right?

31:37.210 --> 31:39.420
It was over the minute
I heard Megan was alive.

31:39.420 --> 31:40.750
Well, then,
why not tell her?

31:40.750 --> 31:42.960
If it's so over, why are
you keeping it a secret?

31:42.960 --> 31:45.210
Owen: Maybe because
she's been through enough
pain for one lifetime?

31:45.210 --> 31:47.880
Exactly! Look, there's no reason
to put her through it.

31:47.880 --> 31:50.540
That is such B.S.

31:50.540 --> 31:52.620
I am sorry, but I have
been there with you.

31:52.620 --> 31:54.420
I have been the person
that found out too late

31:54.420 --> 31:55.620
that there was
a thing with Meredith,

31:55.620 --> 31:57.250
and it just makes
everything worse --

31:57.250 --> 31:58.540
for everyone.

31:58.540 --> 32:00.000
Okay, we were just
trying to protect you.

32:00.000 --> 32:01.080
Well, I didn't need
your protection.

32:01.080 --> 32:02.580
I needed information.

32:02.580 --> 32:04.120
Thank you.

32:04.120 --> 32:05.540
I am Meredith's sister,

32:05.540 --> 32:09.120
so if there are sides to be
taken here, I am on hers.

32:09.120 --> 32:11.580
Just tell your fiancée
the truth, Nathan.

32:11.580 --> 32:13.420
'Cause she doesn't want
your pity or your protection.

32:13.420 --> 32:15.880
What she wants
is your respect.

32:17.710 --> 32:19.380
[ Door opens ]
Wait.

32:19.380 --> 32:22.120
You had a thing
with Meredith's sister, too?

32:24.880 --> 32:27.830
Teddy Altman thinks I'm wrong
to do Megan's surgery.

32:27.830 --> 32:30.000
Well, since when do you care
what Teddy Altman thinks?

32:30.000 --> 32:31.540
[ Bicycle bell dings ]
Well...I don't.

32:33.830 --> 32:36.460
But she thinks I'm wrong,
and Amelia's on my side,

32:36.460 --> 32:37.710
and Amelia
is a little crazy.

32:39.750 --> 32:42.920
No one asked me to do it.
I did insert myself.

32:42.920 --> 32:45.920
Why did I do that?

32:45.920 --> 32:48.120
Because you're trying
to be the surgeon
you wish Derek had had.

32:48.120 --> 32:50.670
[ Ship horn blows ]

32:50.670 --> 32:52.670
You need to tell Jo

32:52.670 --> 32:54.460
that you hired someone
to find that husband of hers.

32:54.460 --> 32:56.210
Why?

32:56.210 --> 32:58.500
You're trying to win
her back, giving her
solo surgeries, right?

32:58.500 --> 33:00.040
Wait.
You heard about that?

33:00.040 --> 33:01.580
Everybody heard about it.

33:01.580 --> 33:03.170
Glasses?

33:03.170 --> 33:04.620
[ Both laugh ]

33:04.620 --> 33:06.330
It was insane.

33:06.330 --> 33:07.580
But she handled
the hell out of it.

33:09.670 --> 33:11.460
Anyway, if you want
to build a future with her,

33:11.460 --> 33:12.790
you really should
tell her the truth.

33:15.040 --> 33:16.920
She deserves the dignity
of the whole story.

33:18.790 --> 33:20.420
Yeah.

33:20.420 --> 33:22.580
I really just don't know why
you didn't get your own lunch.

33:27.040 --> 33:31.420
[ Woman speaking indistinctly
on P.A. ]

33:37.830 --> 33:38.960
Hey.

33:38.960 --> 33:40.080
Hey.

33:40.080 --> 33:42.250
I was avoiding you.

33:42.250 --> 33:44.420
Is that what that was?

33:44.420 --> 33:47.170
I just figured
you were a little --
What?

33:48.500 --> 33:51.790
Odd. Little odd sometimes.
That's all.

33:51.790 --> 33:54.500
[ Inhales sharply ]

33:54.500 --> 33:56.620
I hate when people
don't tell me things.

33:56.620 --> 33:58.290
So, um...

33:58.290 --> 34:01.420
the night of the fire,
April said something to me

34:01.420 --> 34:04.580
about me being into you
and you being into me,

34:04.580 --> 34:06.500
and...it was weird,

34:06.500 --> 34:08.710
and I didn't know
what to do with it, so I...

34:08.710 --> 34:10.290
I was odd.

34:15.830 --> 34:17.670
So...April said what?

34:17.670 --> 34:19.000
Crazy, right?

34:19.000 --> 34:20.330
I know.

34:20.330 --> 34:23.120
Um...great.
Glad we're on the same page.

34:23.120 --> 34:25.210
[ Chuckling ] Yeah.

34:28.330 --> 34:29.620
[ Owen sighs ]

34:31.330 --> 34:32.710
Who's gonna do
the talking?

34:32.710 --> 34:34.290
I'll do it.

34:34.290 --> 34:36.710
But if I don't come out
in 10 minutes, call the police.

34:36.710 --> 34:37.830
[ Chuckles ]

34:44.920 --> 34:46.920
Can you wait outside?

34:46.920 --> 34:48.670
Please?
We need a minute.

34:48.670 --> 34:54.880
♪♪

34:54.880 --> 35:01.120
♪♪

35:01.120 --> 35:03.960
Are you
in love with him?

35:03.960 --> 35:06.500
I had one great love in my life,
and he died.

35:06.500 --> 35:12.620
♪♪

35:12.620 --> 35:13.790
Are you a mother?

35:13.790 --> 35:14.920
I am.

35:17.380 --> 35:19.330
I need to
get back to my son.

35:19.330 --> 35:22.460
And I want to do everything
I can to make sure that happens.

35:22.460 --> 35:29.210
♪♪

35:29.210 --> 35:30.710
Nathan has
excellent taste in women.

35:33.920 --> 35:36.000
He certainly does.

35:36.000 --> 35:38.120
♪♪

35:44.380 --> 35:46.500
♪♪

35:46.500 --> 35:48.920
[ Chuckles ]

35:48.920 --> 35:50.880
Ortho wrapped up yesterday.

35:50.880 --> 35:53.580
Then vascular came in,
did some work on the walls.

35:53.580 --> 35:54.790
This is...

35:54.790 --> 35:55.790
The plastics posse.

35:55.790 --> 35:58.000
Precisely.

35:58.000 --> 35:59.460
Mm.

35:59.460 --> 36:01.580
[ Slurping ]

36:04.120 --> 36:05.710
Stop worrying.

36:05.710 --> 36:08.750
Dr. Grey is a bigger man
than either of you.

36:08.750 --> 36:10.620
She'll forgive us
eventually, right? Huh.

36:10.620 --> 36:12.380
[ Chuckles ]

36:12.380 --> 36:13.750
Amelia: It'll be
a long surgery.

36:13.750 --> 36:16.040
We'll have to
take apart his jaw

36:16.040 --> 36:18.120
and then take out the tumor
slowly and carefully

36:18.120 --> 36:19.790
to avoid
damaging the nerves.

36:19.790 --> 36:22.580
And we will have to wean him off
some of his painkillers.

36:22.580 --> 36:24.790
But you think you can do it?
You can take the tumor out?

36:24.790 --> 36:25.710
Yes.

36:26.750 --> 36:28.120
I think I can.

36:30.880 --> 36:33.120
[ Monitor beeping ]

36:35.120 --> 36:37.170
Okay,
just one more time.

36:37.170 --> 36:39.120
We'll start
by lysing the adhesions

36:39.120 --> 36:40.460
to free up the bowel.

36:40.460 --> 36:42.620
And then take down
the EC fistula.

36:42.620 --> 36:45.000
After which,
we'll reverse the colostomy.

36:45.000 --> 36:46.880
Phew!

36:46.880 --> 36:48.420
More nervous
than I expected.

36:48.420 --> 36:51.380
Well, that's not a bad thing.
Just means you care.

36:51.380 --> 36:52.790
[ Water running ]

36:52.790 --> 36:55.670
Excuse me.
Excuse me.

36:55.670 --> 36:57.000
Hey.

36:58.460 --> 37:00.500
Oh. Thanks.

37:00.500 --> 37:02.330
She's gonna do great.

37:02.330 --> 37:04.000
10 blade.

37:04.000 --> 37:06.040
[ Lowell's "War Face" plays ]

37:08.790 --> 37:10.750
♪ Ooh ♪

37:10.750 --> 37:13.000
♪ Ooh ♪

37:13.000 --> 37:16.420
♪ Love fades like a wave ♪

37:16.420 --> 37:18.540
♪ Changing seasons ♪

37:18.540 --> 37:20.670
♪ Pull up my sleeves and ♪

37:20.670 --> 37:22.620
♪ I got my bourbon ♪

37:22.620 --> 37:24.290
♪ I got my Jack and ♪

37:24.290 --> 37:26.080
[ Italian accent ]
You drinking alone?

37:28.170 --> 37:30.540
I was ghosted --
by my girlfriend.

37:30.540 --> 37:32.080
Mm.

37:32.080 --> 37:33.420
Do you know what that means --
Ghosted?

37:33.420 --> 37:35.420
Si.
She disappeared.

37:35.420 --> 37:36.790
Why am I the only person
that doesn't --

37:36.790 --> 37:39.080
W-When did this
become something

37:39.080 --> 37:41.000
that people do
to other people?

37:41.000 --> 37:42.710
I think it's because
of the Internet.

37:42.710 --> 37:45.250
We yell to our friends
and family on Facebook

37:45.250 --> 37:47.710
in ways we would never do
across a dinner table.

37:47.710 --> 37:50.540
We become, um, uh...
rude.

37:50.540 --> 37:51.790
Unsensitive.

37:51.790 --> 37:53.790
-"Insensitive."
-Insensitive.

37:53.790 --> 37:55.920
[ Chuckling ] Forget it.
I like your way better.

37:55.920 --> 37:56.920
♪ Ooh, ooh ♪

37:56.920 --> 37:59.040
♪ You left me bleedin' ♪

37:59.040 --> 38:01.210
♪ Got away with treason ♪

38:01.210 --> 38:05.500
♪ I led the battle
into the trenches ♪

38:05.500 --> 38:07.420
♪ I learned my lesson ♪

38:07.420 --> 38:09.420
♪ I count my blessings ♪

38:09.420 --> 38:11.750
♪ You had me howlin' ♪

38:11.750 --> 38:14.080
♪ You had me howlin' ♪

38:14.080 --> 38:17.960
♪ You had me howlin'
at the moon ♪

38:17.960 --> 38:20.120
♪ Oh, yeah, I'm howlin' ♪

38:20.120 --> 38:22.290
♪ Oh, yeah, I'm howlin' ♪

38:22.290 --> 38:25.710
♪ Oh, yeah, I'm howlin',
but not for you ♪

38:25.710 --> 38:26.790
♪ Ooh-ooh-ooh ♪

38:26.790 --> 38:30.460
♪♪

38:30.460 --> 38:32.580
♪ I wear my war face ♪

38:32.580 --> 38:34.790
♪ I wear my war face ♪

38:34.790 --> 38:36.540
♪ I wear my war face ♪

38:36.540 --> 38:38.960
♪ And I'm never gonna
take you back again ♪

38:38.960 --> 38:41.750
♪ I wear my war face,
I wear my war face ♪

38:41.750 --> 38:43.620
[ Bells jingle ]

38:43.620 --> 38:45.250
♪ I wear my war face ♪

38:45.250 --> 38:47.250
Hey.
Can I talk to you?

38:47.250 --> 38:49.250
[ Sighs ]
Please don't.

38:49.250 --> 38:51.540
Don't?

38:51.540 --> 38:53.670
I'm still in love
with Alex.

38:53.670 --> 38:55.290
And I know
that he hurt you,

38:55.290 --> 38:58.000
and I know that
he's...volatile,

38:58.000 --> 38:59.250
and I know that
I can't be with him,

38:59.250 --> 39:00.960
but I can't be
with you, either.

39:00.960 --> 39:02.880
And we work together,
so can we just --

39:02.880 --> 39:05.120
Can we please just not
make it awkward?

39:07.710 --> 39:09.500
I wanted to...
talk about the fact

39:09.500 --> 39:11.330
that I'm worried about
Dr. Shepherd.

39:11.330 --> 39:14.540
But...yeah,
let's not make it awkward.

39:14.540 --> 39:15.790
♪♪

39:15.790 --> 39:17.210
[ Bells jingle ]

39:17.210 --> 39:19.750
♪ Put us back together again ♪

39:19.750 --> 39:20.960
I would like to pay
for your drink.

39:20.960 --> 39:22.420
Oh, my...

39:22.420 --> 39:24.210
By...way of apology?

39:24.210 --> 39:25.790
[ Exhales deeply ]

39:25.790 --> 39:28.460
For your surgery
the other day?

39:28.460 --> 39:29.710
Yes! I remember.

39:29.710 --> 39:32.540
You should probably
buy contact lenses.

39:32.540 --> 39:35.000
Already put in
the order.

39:35.000 --> 39:38.170
And for whatever it's worth,
you handled that like a boss.

39:41.710 --> 39:43.830
My friend moved away.

39:43.830 --> 39:45.790
And that surgery --

39:45.790 --> 39:47.670
she would've been
so impressed with me.

39:47.670 --> 39:49.620
Mm.

39:49.620 --> 39:51.380
[ Laughing ] And we would've
laughed really hard

39:51.380 --> 39:52.710
at your expense.
[ Laughs ]

39:52.710 --> 39:56.380
I will totally laugh with you
at my own expense.

39:56.380 --> 39:58.790
And then
she would've reminded me

39:58.790 --> 40:02.330
of all the reasons
it's a terrible idea

40:02.330 --> 40:06.040
to do the one thing that I
really, desperately want to do.

40:07.380 --> 40:08.750
Which is what?

40:08.750 --> 40:11.040
♪ ...and all of my men ♪

40:11.040 --> 40:14.250
♪ Couldn't put us
back together again ♪

40:16.830 --> 40:19.170
[ Exhales deeply ]
What's taking so long?

40:19.170 --> 40:22.290
Well, we knew
it'd be a long wait.

40:22.290 --> 40:24.420
Meredith:
We go to medical school
because we want to learn

40:24.420 --> 40:26.000
how to fix what's broken.

40:26.000 --> 40:28.170
-Where's Amelia?
-What?

40:29.790 --> 40:31.080
Where's your wife, Owen?

40:33.080 --> 40:34.830
Hey, it's done.
Meredith did it.

40:34.830 --> 40:36.000
She's getting
ready to close.

40:36.000 --> 40:37.040
Ha!

40:37.040 --> 40:38.790
[ Laughing ] Yes!

40:38.790 --> 40:41.500
-[ Laughs ]
-Come on.

40:41.500 --> 40:43.580
But we quickly learn

40:43.580 --> 40:45.120
that we often
have to make things worse

40:45.120 --> 40:46.500
before we can make them better.

40:49.210 --> 40:50.290
[ Sighs ] Ohh!

40:50.290 --> 40:51.670
[ Laughs ] Sorry.

40:51.670 --> 40:52.920
Andrea?

40:52.920 --> 40:53.920
Carina?

40:53.920 --> 40:55.040
[ Speaking Italian ]

40:55.040 --> 40:57.540
[ Speaking Italian ]

40:57.540 --> 40:58.830
[ Speaking Italian ]

40:58.830 --> 41:01.000
[ Speaking Italian ]

41:01.000 --> 41:03.670
[ Both shouting in Italian ]

41:08.380 --> 41:10.380
[ Shouting continues ]

41:10.380 --> 41:17.830
♪♪

41:23.620 --> 41:25.120
[ Gasps ]
Oh! Sorry.

41:25.120 --> 41:26.380
[ Sighs ]

41:26.380 --> 41:28.460
Maybe just, um,
take them off?

41:28.460 --> 41:31.670
It's risky and it's frightening
for surgeons and for patients,

41:31.670 --> 41:33.290
but usually, it's worth it.

41:34.960 --> 41:36.710
You get
a second chance at life,

41:36.710 --> 41:39.380
and we get to be the architects
of your second chance.

41:39.380 --> 41:42.880
[ Monitor beeping ]

41:42.880 --> 41:44.580
It's win-win.

41:44.580 --> 41:45.790
What's going on?

41:45.790 --> 41:48.170
[ Beeping continues ]

41:48.170 --> 41:50.420
When it works.
Meredith!

41:50.420 --> 41:53.830
There isn't enough tissue.
I can't close.

41:53.830 --> 41:56.080
[ Beeping continues ]

42:04.670 --> 42:05.960
Damn it!

42:05.960 --> 42:08.120
[ Beeping continues ]
